Job Description-

This role will blend business acumen with technical proficiency, requiring the ability to understand complex business processes and translate them into effective system configurations. You will be a key player in ensuring our systems accurately reflect business needs and operate efficiently. This position will focus heavily on the developing new processes with technical solutions with the vehicle configuration space. The position will utilize ML and AI to quickly develop solutions.

 • Collaborate with stakeholders across various departments to understand business needs, gather detailed requirements, and document them clearly and concisely using various techniques (e.g., user stories, use cases, process flows). 

• Translate business requirements into technical configurations within our [mention specific system] backend. This includes, but is not limited to:

 • Developing and maintaining configuration specifications.

 • Creating and modifying data mappings and integrations.

 • Implementing and testing new configurations.

 • Troubleshooting and resolving configuration-related issues. 

• Analyze existing data to identify trends, inefficiencies, and areas for improvement. This may involve querying databases, generating reports, and visualizing data using appropriate tools. 

• Identify opportunities to streamline business processes and improve system efficiency through configuration changes and best practices. 

• Thoroughly test configurations to ensure they meet requirements and function as expected. Participate in user acceptance testing (UAT). 

• Maintain comprehensive documentation of system configurations, processes, and troubleshooting steps. 

• Work closely with developers, IT support, and other stakeholders to ensure smooth implementation and ongoing support of system configurations.

Skills Required:

-Strong analytical and problem-solving skills. -Excellent communication, interpersonal, and collaboration skills. -Ability to translate complex technical information into easily understandable terms for non-technical audiences.

Skills Preferred:

-Java experience -SQL experience

Experience Required:

-ML experience and implementation experience

Experience Preferred:

-Experience with Agile methodologies is a plus. -Experience with vehicle configuration is a plus.

Role Overview:
This role is a critical link between business operations and technical implementation, responsible for translating complex organizational requirements into effective system configurations and solutions. As a key member of the team, you will leverage your strong analytical skills, technical proficiency, and collaborative mindset to drive process improvements and ensure the seamless integration of business needs with technology. Your ability to bridge the gap between stakeholders and developers will be instrumental in delivering efficient and user-friendly systems that support the organization's growth and success.

Key Responsibilities:
- Collaborate closely with stakeholders across various departments to thoroughly understand business requirements, document them using industry-standard techniques (e.g., user stories, use cases, process flows), and communicate them effectively to the technical team.
- Translate business requirements into detailed technical configurations within the [mention specific system] backend, including developing and maintaining configuration specifications, creating and modifying data mappings and integrations, implementing and testing new configurations, and troubleshooting any related issues.
- Analyze existing data to identify trends, inefficiencies, and areas for improvement, utilizing tools such as database querying, report generation, and data visualization.
- Proactively identify opportunities to streamline business processes and enhance system efficiency through configuration changes and the implementation of industry best practices.
- Thoroughly test configurations to ensure they meet requirements and function as expected, and actively participate in user acceptance testing (UAT) processes.
- Maintain comprehensive documentation of system configurations, processes, and troubleshooting steps to support ongoing operations and future enhancements.
- Collaborate closely with developers, IT support, and other stakeholders to ensure the smooth implementation and continuous support of system configurations.

Required Skills:
- Strong analytical and problem-solving skills to effectively translate complex business requirements into technical solutions.
- Excellent communication, interpersonal, and collaboration skills to bridge the gap between business and technical teams.
- Ability to translate complex technical information into easily understandable terms for non-technical audiences.
- Proficiency in data analysis and reporting, leveraging tools and techniques to identify areas for improvement.

Preferred Skills:
- Experience with Java programming language to enhance your technical capabilities.
- Familiarity with SQL to efficiently query and manipulate data as part of the configuration process.

Required Experience:
- Proven track record in implementing and configuring complex enterprise systems, with a strong understanding of business processes and technical requirements.
- Experience in leveraging machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) technologies to develop efficient and innovative solutions.

Preferred Experience:
- Familiarity with Agile methodologies and their application in a fast-paced, collaborative environment.
- Previous exposure to the vehicle configuration domain, providing a deeper understanding of the industry-specific challenges and requirements.

Tools & Technologies:
- [Mention specific system] backend configuration tools
- Data analysis and reporting software (e.g., SQL, Power BI, Tableau)
- Collaboration and documentation tools (e.g., Jira, Confluence)

Work Environment & Expectations:
- Collaborative, cross-functional team environment with regular communication and feedback.
- Ability to work independently and as part of a team to drive project deliverables.
- Willingness to learn and adapt to new technologies and methodologies as the organization evolves.
- Demonstrated commitment to continuous improvement and process optimization.
